The paper discusses the use of computational models to predict the difficulty of Sudoku puzzles, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the evaluation of the difficulty rating metrics involves analyzing human problem solving behavior, which relates to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the complexity of individual steps and the structure of dependency among steps, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach inspired by phase transition phenomenon in the graph coloring problem, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
